cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.DC 

This paper deals with the problem of mitigating interference in vehicle-to-vehicle (V2V) broadcast communication, which is a topic related to networked systems (cs.NI) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also formulates the problem as a mixed integer programming problem, which is a topic related to control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper proposes heuristic algorithms to handle larger instances of the problem, which is a topic related to multimedia (cs.MM) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
